<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36081e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36081e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36081e"> 81(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Pico Lage / Huruhuba / Calabou&ccedil;o</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The entrance to the bay, between the Sugar Loaf on the W. and the <mark>Pico</mark> on the E., with fortress of Santa Cruz on one side and the fort of S&atilde;o J&atilde; on the other, is about a mile wide and free from obstructions. Almost midway in the channel are the little island and fort of <mark>Lage</mark> &hellip; on the E. the almost landlocked bay of <mark>Jurujuba</mark> &hellip; extends northward between the arsenal of war (<i><mark>Ponta do Calabou&ccedil;o</mark></i>) and the opposite Ponta da Gravat&aacute;, of about 3500 yds. <small> &ldquo;RIO DE JANEIRO&rdquo; <a name="EBRO" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EBRO"><cite title="source">Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 353d</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
